<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1837,2043]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,647]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="160" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2460219442" collectionCode="RBINS" collectorName="J. L. Hellman &amp; Coll. A. Knisch &amp; A. d'Orchymont &amp; P. D. Perkins &amp; P. D. Perkins." country="Brazil" determinerName="Kniz" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="160" location="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" specimenCount="11" typeStatus="syntype">
The 
<collectionCode box="[204,286,1837,1863]" country="Belgium" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35271" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35271" name="Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" type="Museum">RBINS</collectionCode>
kindly provided seven 
<typeStatus box="[559,657,1837,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[699,1036,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis box="[699,945,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Hydrochus purpureus</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
, which are part of the Orchymont/ Knisch types collection. The 
<typeStatus box="[473,571,1873,1899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">syntypes</typeStatus>
consist of three males, three females, and one specimen of unknown gender (a prior worker dissected the specimen, but there are no apical genital segments or male genitalia with the specimen). One of the 
<typeStatus box="[275,362,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">syntype</typeStatus>
females bears a 
<typeStatus box="[546,649,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">lectotype</typeStatus>
label, by 
<collectorName box="[757,911,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">J. L. Hellman</collectorName>
, but this designation was never published. This label has been reversed and “unpub.” written on the reverse side. There are at least three species represented by the 
<typeStatus box="[151,253,2017,2043]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The males represent two species which markedly differ externally, and the male genitalia also distinctively differ. I have selected one of the two males from 
<collectingCountry box="[696,767,153,179]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, “Matto Grosso,” to serve as 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1199,153,179]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
, have labeled it such, and have imaged the habitus, male genitalia and labels of this specimen (
<figureCitation box="[962,1039,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1555,1580]" captionTargetBox="[174,1425,194,1480]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,181,1529]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hydrochus purpureus Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557943/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1052,1102,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1786,1811]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,197,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1435,181,1761]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13A–E. Labels of lectotypes and neotype. (A) Hydrochus metallipes Knisch; (B) Hydrochus pumilio Knisch; (C) Hydrochus purpureus Knisch; (D) Hydrochus tarsalis Chevrolat; (E) Hydrochus secretus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557953/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">13C</figureCitation>
). The other male from “Matto Grosso” is conspecific with the 
<typeStatus box="[507,613,225,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The third male, clearly a different species, is from 
<collectingCountry box="[1186,1300,225,251]" name="Argentina" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and bears a label “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bruch A. d'Orchym. Rev." box="[225,746,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Hydrous" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corruscans">
<emphasis box="[225,450,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Hydrous corruscans</emphasis>
Bruch A. d’Orchym. Rev.
</taxonomicName>
” 
<typeStatus box="[762,874,261,287]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Lectotype</typeStatus>
labels (
<figureCitation box="[961,1064,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1786,1811]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,197,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1435,181,1761]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13A–E. Labels of lectotypes and neotype. (A) Hydrochus metallipes Knisch; (B) Hydrochus pumilio Knisch; (C) Hydrochus purpureus Knisch; (D) Hydrochus tarsalis Chevrolat; (E) Hydrochus secretus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557953/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
): “Bras.Corumba [Matto Grosso] // 
<collectorName box="[175,352,297,323]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Coll. A. Knisch</collectorName>
COTYPUS // det. 
<determinerName box="[571,625,297,323]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Kniž</determinerName>
<emphasis box="[634,748,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">purpureus</emphasis>
// coll. 
<collectorName box="[837,1014,297,323]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">A.d’Orchymont</collectorName>
// HABITUS/GENIT. DIGITAL IM- AGES captured 2019 
<collectorName box="[402,541,333,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">P.D. Perkins</collectorName>
// [red] 
<typeStatus box="[636,796,333,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[804,1135,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis box="[804,1048,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Hydrochus purpureus</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
desig. 
<collectorName box="[1218,1376,333,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">P. D. Perkins.</collectorName>
” The six non-lectotype 
<typeStatus box="[352,450,369,395]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">syntypes</typeStatus>
have been labeled 
<typeStatus box="[664,829,369,395]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="160" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[373,479,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
, plus the second male from 
<collectingRegion box="[797,945,405,431]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, one of the females from 
<collectingRegion box="[1235,1384,405,431]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, and the 
<typeStatus box="[196,283,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">syntype</typeStatus>
of unknown gender distinctively differ from the other 
<typeStatus box="[925,1023,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">syntypes</typeStatus>
in having a deep cervical sulcus, a groove behind the eyes into which fits the arcuate anterior margin of the pronotum (for descriptions of other species with this character see Perkins, in press). This rather obvious character has not been mentioned by previous authors, including 
<bibRefCitation author="Makhan, D." box="[265,442,549,575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160" pagination="95 - 103" refId="ref5661" refString="Makhan, D. (1992) Twelve new Hydrochus - species from South America. Phegea, 20 (2), 95 - 103." type="journal article" year="1992">Makhan (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[454,600,549,575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160" pagination="87 - 104" refId="ref6088" refString="Oliva, A. (1992) The species of Hydrochus (Coleoptera; Hydrophiloidea; Hydrochidae) described from South America. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 128, 87 - 104." type="journal article" year="1992">Oliva (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, in the “Material examined” section listed six 
<typeStatus box="[1124,1225,549,575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">syntypes</typeStatus>
, but did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[228,334,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The description in 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[563,709,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160" pagination="87 - 104" refId="ref6088" refString="Oliva, A. (1992) The species of Hydrochus (Coleoptera; Hydrophiloidea; Hydrochidae) described from South America. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 128, 87 - 104." type="journal article" year="1992">Oliva (1992)</bibRefCitation>
cannot be conclusively evaluated because it is unknown which 
<typeStatus box="[151,238,621,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="160">syntype</typeStatus>
was used for the description, or if the description is a composite based on two or more specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
